content:
I see the bug — you're calling `bcrypt.hash(password)` without the salt rounds argument. That causes bcrypt to use an undefined value and the hash comes out wrong.

Fixed in `src/auth/password.js`:
```js
// Before (broken):
const hash = await bcrypt.hash(password);

// After (correct):
const SALT_ROUNDS = 12;
const hash = await bcrypt.hash(password, SALT_ROUNDS);
```

Salt rounds = 12 is a good balance between security and latency (~300ms on modern hardware). The existing test in `tests/auth/password.test.js` now passes.
